This note is just a reminder that TUESDAY, September 8 is the last day for Distance Learning for Beggs Public Schools.

Elementary and Middle School students will return to class on WEDNESDAY, September 9.

The High School has Virtual Wednesdays, so high school students will return to in-person class on THURSDAY, September 10.

ATTENTION: IMPORTANT COVID-19 UPDATE FOR ALL BEGGS SCHOOLS:

We have been gathering information over the past few hours, so we apologize for the timing of this notice.

Due to several students and staff members testing positive for COVID-19, Beggs Public Schools will move to distance learning through September 8th. This is for all students: elementary, middle, and high school students.

Elementary and middle school students will return to in-person teaching on September 9th.

High school will have a Virtual Wednesday on September 9 and return to in-person classes on September 10.

For middle school and high school activities:
The directors and coaches will be in touch with their groups to inform you if practice will continue, games will be held, or FFA shows will continue.

Principals and teachers will share grade level information separately.

It is important that we keep the health and safety of our students at the center of all of our decisions. Thank you for your continued support as we all work through this together.

Beggs High School
August 28 at 11:11 AM ·

BHS HOME FOOTBALL GAME NEW PROTOCOLS DUE TO COVID-19:

Fans will not be able to be on the football field BEFORE the game for the spirit tunnel.

Also, fans will not be able to be on the football field AFTER the game for the team meeting.

We understand that these traditions are very meaningful to our team and our community. However, we cannot take the risk of possibly spreading the COVID-19 virus. The last thing we want to happen is for our team to be forced to quarantine because of an outbreak. Please help us keep our team healthy. We appreciate your understanding and cooperation.

shared_text:
Green Country Technology Center
August 13 at 12:11 PM ·

As we prepare for the return of full-time students to our campus, GCTC’s top priority is the safety and well being of our students, teachers, staff and all stakeholders. With that in mind, PHASE IV of our Mitigation Plan will follow the guidelines provided by the CDC as well as the Oklahoma State Department of Health’s COVID-19 Alert System.

PHASE IV will include all prior Phases I, II & III with the addition of the new Return to Learn Plans and guidelines which can be found on our website.

- GCTC’S COVID-19 Alert System color chart
- Student Guide Return to Learning – GREEN (New Normal)
- Student Guide Return to Learning – YELLOW (Low Risk)
- Student Guide Return to Learning – ORANGE (Moderate Risk)
- Student Guide Return to Learning – RED (High Risk)

Please note, when full-time classes begin on August 24, our school will begin in the ORANGE ZONE.

Please refer to our website for downloadable documents and details.

https://www.gctcok.edu/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1682277&type=d&pREC_ID=1862751

post_text:
NEW START DATE for Beggs Schools

Due to the overwhelming duties to ensure our virtual and blended programs are implemented appropriately at the same time as our traditional classrooms, the school board has voted to move the start date of school to Thursday, August 20.

HIGH SCHOOL ONLY: Beggs High School students who are attending traditional classes on campus will have Virtual Wednesdays. This means that high school students come to class as normal on Monday and Tuesday, then stay at home Wednesday for virtual learning, then come back to campus for Thursday and Friday. This schedule will ensure that teachers have the appropriate time to meet with all virtual students whether they are online at home, blended, or traditional students.

Preview Night for elementary and high school students will still be Tuesday, August 11, from 5-7pm.

We appreciate the Beggs Board of Education supporting the administration, teachers, and staff of our school in our quest to do what’s in the best interest of our students.

Beggs Public Schools would like to welcome Shawn Tennyson as the new superintendent for the 2020-2021 school year. If seven really is a lucky number, then good things are coming to Beggs as Tennyson will begin his 7th year as a school superintendent.

Tennyson grew up in the Enid area and graduated from Enid High School. He began his college career in Dallas at Dallas Christian College where he was a walk on for the basketball team. Later, an injury sent him back to Oklahoma where he earned a bachelor’s degree in elementary education from Phillips University. While at Phillips, he earned a scholarship playing drums in the band. He later earned a master’s degree in administration from…

Beggs Public Schools would like to share the memorial service information for Mr. Bob Lovett.

Mr. Lovett worked for Beggs Schools as a geography, history, and band teacher for 30+ years and retired in the early 2000’s.

His service will be Tuesday, June 30, at Stanley Funeral Home at 1pm. Public viewing is Monday from 2-4pm. The address of the funeral home is 3959 E. 31st Street in Tulsa.

We wish to offer our condolences to the family during this difficult time.

Beggs Elementary & Beggs Middle school NEW & RETURNING Student Enrollment Information for the 2020-2021 school year:
BES & BMS will have drive-thru enrollment for Pre-K thru 4th grade at BES and for 5th-8th grade at BMS the week of June 8-11 from 10 am-Noon M-Th and Tuesday evening, June 9 from 5-7 pm. THIS IS INSTEAD OF PICKING UP ENROLLMENT PACKETS on Preview Night for BES students & INSTEAD OF Enrolllment Day in Aug for BMS students. Parents can drive-thru the driveway and get the grade level packets needed and park in the parking lot. When forms are complete, parents can hold up the clipboards and a teacher will retrieve them. This is also when teachers can make copies of any documents needed in the office. For example, new students must show proof of residency by submitting a utility bill, birth certificate, updated shot records, along with CDIB or Tribal cards.
7th grade enrollment students will need to get the Tdap immunization and bring their shot record by August 3rd. See you then! Thank you for doing this earlier than usual in these uncharted times.

post_text: Thank you Tricia Buttram and students and families! You are the best! THANK YOU FOR THE THOUGHTFULNESS AND LOVE!
shared_text:
Tricia Buttram
April 11 at 11:34 AM ·

One amazing thing about being in a small town is that when anything happens, good or bad, we are able to lean and depend on each other. Even though school ended suddenly the amazing teachers and administrators have made sure our babies have felt loved and remembered no matter what.

A week ago, I saw a news story where another town’s teachers made a video for their students. Since our teachers have already done so much I thought we could do something similar for them. I made a group and posted an invitation, and obviously the response was overwhelming.

I hope this shows some truly amazing people that what they do does not go unnoticed. School or no school we will get through this together, because #wearebeggs

(I do not own the rights to this music, just knew it would be perfect)
text:
Thank you Tricia Buttram and students and families! You are the best! THANK YOU FOR THE THOUGHTFULNESS AND LOVE!

April 11 at 11:34 AM ·

One amazing thing about being in a small town is that when anything happens, good or bad, we are able to lean and depend on each other. Even though school ended suddenly the amazing teachers and administrators have made sure our babies have felt loved and remembered no matter what.

A week ago, I saw a news story where another town’s teachers made a video for their students. Since our teachers have already done so much I thought we could do something similar for them. I made a group and posted an invitation, and obviously the response was overwhelming.

I hope this shows some truly amazing people that what they do does not go unnoticed. School or no school we will get through this together, because #wearebeggs

(I do not own the rights to this music, just knew it would be perfect)

Students, Parents, and Families,

Due to the “safe at home” order, we are unable to go to classrooms to get devices to check out for student use. We have been given strict directives from the state department to not allow teachers or students into the building to retrieve anything. As we understand the order, it is now in effect until April 30. We understand the hardship this places on families and sympathize with everyone's situation. Please do the best you can with what you have available at home.

The elementary, middle, and high schools will have their distance learning lessons posted on Monday, April 6. There will be an online version and a paper packet version. Please be patient with us as we work out all the kinks. This is the first time for all of us, and we will work through it together. It’s STILL a great day to be a Demon!!

I am arranging a drive thru medication pick-up

When: Monday, March 30 and Tuesday March 31. 8-10 am.
Where: Beggs Elementary Pre-K doors

Procedure: Please call my office at 918.267.0507 to let me know you are on the way. Give me the name of the student and approximate time of arrival. When you get here, call again and I will bring the meds to your car.

All medication from High School, Middle School, and Elementary will be distributed at the Elementary location.

ALL MEDICATION (MEDS, EPI-PENS, INHALERS) NOT PICKED UP WILL BE DISPOSED OF.

I know this is all so crazy! I appreciate your patience. I miss your kids and am looking forward to seeing them next year.

Karen Freeman RN BSN

post_text:
To encourage more families to take advantage of the healthy choices available for school breakfast, Beggs Public Schools will celebrate National School Breakfast Week during March 2-6, 2020.

Busy weekday mornings make it a challenge for many families to find time for a healthy breakfast. However, US Department of Agriculture data show that more and more students are starting their day with a nutritious breakfast in their school cafeterias. The USDA School Breakfast Program currently serves more than 14 million students every day. Studies show that students who eat school breakfast are more likely to:

Reach higher levels of achievement in reading and math
Score higher on standardized tests…

PRE-KINDERGARTEN & KINDERGARTEN FOR FALL 2020 ENROLLMENT FOR STUDENTS NEW TO BES
Pre-Kindergarten & Kindergarten pre-enrollment for students new to Beggs is scheduled for April 2 & 3. Pre-K students must be 4 on or before Sept. 1. Kindergarten students must be 5 on or before Sept. 1. Please call the BES office to schedule an appointment, 918-267-3631. Please bring the following to your appointment: Birth Certificate, Social Security card, CDIB card, and Tribal Enrollment card, Immunization record, and current utility bill for proof of residency. You will fill out an enrollment form for the office at your appointment. Thank you!

post_text:
At this time, Beggs will have school tomorrow. We are monitoring the water situation and understand your concerns.
We do our best to get information to our parents and our community in a timely manner. We ask for your understanding in these cases that are out of our control. If or when school needs to be cancelled, parents and guardians will know as soon as we know. We will post on Facebook, send text messages out through our Enote service, and contact the local television stations. Thank you for your patience as we all work through this together.

Veterans Day is November 11, 2019. Beggs Public Schools is planning their annual assembly and would like to invite and honor our community's veterans and active duty military members. Please contact us if you would like to attend our assembly and be recognized for your service to our country. We would love to have you!!
Please email Autumn Caldwell: acaldwell@beggs.k12.ok.us if you are a veteran or active military and can attend. She will send you a short information sheet to be completed.
Deadline is November 1st to contact Mrs. Caldwell about attending the assembly. Thank you!!

Veterans Day Assembly
Date: November 11, 2019
Time: 1:40pm - 2:30pm
Place: Beggs Event Center

post_text: BES brought back Career Day and what a success it was!!! Many thanks to BES Counselor Ms. Long and all the amazing volunteers that came to share their jobs with our students on this beautiful fall day! We had firemen, policemen, officers from the Okmulgee Sheriff's dept, Channel 6's Tess Maune, Wildlife Dept. and Water Commission, EMTs, Airline Pilot, Roller Skate Rink Owner, an Eye Doctor, a Vet Tech, East Central Electric, American Heritage Bank, and the YMCA director. Several of our presenters were former Beggs students, that is so awesome! Thanks again for making it fantastic!

Beggs Middle School is happy to announce today starts our Merritt's Bakery Cheesecake Sale! Students will be bringing home order forms today and they will need to be returned with the money by September 27th.

Single Flavor Cheesecakes are $22 - Turtle, Chocolate, New York Style, Red Velvet, Pumpkin and Strawberry Swirl.

Sampler Cheesecake is $23 and includes 2 slices of New York Style, Chocolate, Strawberry Swirl and Turtle.

These will arrive before Thanksgiving!

If you would like to order but don't know a BMS student please call the office at 918-267-4916.

Thank you for supporting BMS!!!!!
